    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-04-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-04-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="594"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d594">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Thompson</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-04-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 12, 1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Gresham instructs Mr. Thompson, in reply to the latter’s telegram of the
                    10th, to demand—without waiving the right to demand at <pb facs="0734" n="626"
                        xml:id="pg_626"/> a later date that the offenders be punished—that the
                    school be granted a license and full protection, a permit be issued to
                    immediately rebuild, and payment of the full value of the burned building
                    effected.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
